    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eastern Han artifacts, money trees were good luck charms placed in tombs; so named because of their cast bronze branches laden with leaves made of coins. The branches also contain mythological figures and objects important to Han belief.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
